---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '~/lib/siteConfig'
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`About — ${SITE_CONFIG.name}`}
  description={`About ${SITE_CONFIG.name}: ${SITE_CONFIG.tagline}.`}
>
  <header class="container-prose page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">{SITE_CONFIG.name}</a> / About</p>
    <h1>About {SITE_CONFIG.name}</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="container-prose prose">
    <p class="lede">
      <strong>{SITE_CONFIG.name}</strong> is a static catalog of 750+ card
      profiles issued in India — credit, debit, and prepaid — with fees,
      rewards, eligibility, and small-print on each.
    </p>

    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      Banks publish their card terms across PDFs, microsites, and FAQ pages
      that change without notice. {SITE_CONFIG.name} pulls those into a
      single, searchable, comparable form — open data, open source, no
      affiliate gating.
    </p>
    <p>
      Coverage today: 36+ issuers including Amex, Axis, AU SFB, Bandhan, BoB,
      BoM, Canara, CUB, DCB, Dhanlaxmi, ESAF, Federal, HDFC, HSBC, ICICI, IDBI,
      IDFC, Indian Bank, IndusInd, IOB, J&K Bank, Karnataka Bank, Kotak, KVB,
      PNB, PSB, RBL, Saraswat, SBI, SIB, StanChart, TMB, UCO, Union, Yes Bank.
    </p>

    <h2>Part of oriz</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE_CONFIG.name} is one site in the <a href="https://oriz.in/">oriz</a>
      family — small, free, and quiet tools by Chirag Singhal. One sign-in
      works across every site (so your saved cards and reading list follow
      you to the blog, the journal, and back).
    </p>

    <h2>Source</h2>
    <p>
      Code:
      <a href="https://github.com/chirag127/oriz-cards">github.com/chirag127/oriz-cards</a>.
      Issues, corrections, and PRs welcome.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      Information here is for reference. It is not financial advice and may
      lag the bank's own page by days or weeks. Always verify on the issuing
      bank's site before applying. See the
      <a href="/legal/disclaimer/">full disclaimer</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-fg-muted); font-size: 0.8125rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .eyebrow a { color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .eyebrow a:hover { color: var(--color-fg); }
  h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0; }
  .prose { padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem; color: var(--color-prose); line-height: 1.75; font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  .prose .lede { font-size: 1.1875rem; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 0 0 2rem; }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
